NEW SECTION — THE MCG ADVANTAGE (place after How It Works)
Eyebrow: WHY MAGNETIC, NOT ELECTRICAL
Headline: The signal that skin can't blur.
Intro line (one sentence): Electrical heart signals get distorted by skin, muscle and fat on the way out. Magnetic fields pass straight through.
Three short cards (headline + one tight line each):

Undistorted by the body — Magnetic signals are not weakened by tissue, skin, or chest-wall thickness.
No contact required — Magnetic sensing needs no electrodes and tolerates a moving body — which is exactly why it can live in a shirt.
Higher resolution — A multi-sensor MCG array captures finer spatial detail than electrical leads.
Closing line (accent): Most cardiac sensors get worse when worn all day. MCG is the one that doesn't.
Visual to generate: a simple side-by-side diagram — left, a wavy distorted "electrical" line passing through layered tissue and arriving degraded; right, a clean "magnetic" line passing straight through unaffected. Minimal, teal, lots of whitespace.


